"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437963","Home Office","false","2015-12-18","<p>The Home Office regularly conducts visits of all asylum accommodation, including hotels used as contingency, in collaboration with our COMPASS providers. The latest inspection of the Brittania Hotel in Wigan by Home Office officials took place on Thursday 10 December 2015.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-12-18T15:03:00.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437963/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437963/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437963/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437963/answer/previousversion/36263","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-12-14","Compass Contracts: Wigan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when officials of her Department last visited the asylum seekers staying at the Britannia Hotel in Wigan.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","19829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437964","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-18","<p>To maintain the UK’s position as a world-leading location to test, develop, and use connected and automated vehicle (CAV) technologies, the Department for Transport is planning a wider review of domestic regulations by Summer 2017.</p><br /><p>The Highways Act 1835 will form part of the review, which is at an early stage. No decisions have yet been taken as to which regulatory changes will be necessary to support CAV technologies, or if the review will cover other forms of transport such as Segways or so-called ‘hoverboards’. People are already free to use Segways and ‘hoverboards’ on private land.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-12-18T13:09:51.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437964/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437964/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437964/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-14","Electric Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to amend the Highways Act 1835 to allow the use of hoverboards and segways.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","20031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437965","Home Office","false","2015-12-17","<p>The Home Office introduced exit cecks from 8 April 2015 to provide more comphrehensive information on travel movements across the UK border since that date. My Department has informed the Office of National Statistics that it is considering the use of exit checks data for statistical reporting purposes, and plans to publish an initial report in May 2016. Any data published will be subject to the usual data assurance standards.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-12-17T16:09:54.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437965/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437965/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437965/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-12-14","Immigration Controls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will publish her Department's exit checks data relating to all UK ports and airports for destination (a) within and (b) outside the EU.","false","Biography information for Andrea Jenkyns","Morley and Outwood","Andrea Jenkyns","19792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437966","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-12-17","<p>The UK Government has agreed to provide up to £150m over five years (£30m a year) to support the work of the new legacy bodies proposed in the Stormont House Agreement. We remain committed to establishing the new bodies and I will continue to work with the political parties, Northern Ireland Executive and victims groups to achieve broad consensus for the legislation needed to do this.</p><br />","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-12-17T12:43:51.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437966/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437966/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437966/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-12-14","Police Service of Northern Ireland: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what funding is being made available to the Police Service of Northern Ireland to investigate ongoing legacy issues.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","19844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437967","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-12-17","<p>I met the Victims Commissioner and the Victims and Survivors Forum this week. This Government has made greater progress on legacy issues than any of our predecessors and we remain committed to the delivery of the new bodies under the Stormont House Agreement. We will continue to engage with the political parties, Northern Ireland Executive and victims groups to achieve the consensus needed to bring forward legislation.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-12-17T12:46:10.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437967/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437967/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437967/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-12-14","Terrorism: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, which victims' groups she plans to meet to discuss legacy issues over the next 12 months.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","19795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437968","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-12-17","<p>The UK Government has made clear that it is committed to providing full disclosure to the Historical Investigations Unit (HIU) for the purpose of its investigations. This will give the HIU access to very sensitive information, including information which would, if disclosed generally, damage the UK’s national security and put lives at risk.</p><p>As acknowledged in the Stormont House Agreement, the UK Government has a duty to ensure that sensitive information is not released publicly where to do so would put lives or national security at risk.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-12-17T12:48:36.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437968/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437968/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437968/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-12-14","Terrorism: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what assessment she has made of the adequacy of her powers contained in the Stormont House Agreement to determine what can be disclosed to victims' families.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","20044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437969","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-16","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 24 November 2015 to Question UIN16531.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-16T15:31:45.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437969/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437969/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437969/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-14","Unemployment: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he has taken to assist unemployed people over the age of 50 back in to work; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","19943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437970","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-14","<p>All employers in England will be able to access funding for apprenticeships after the introduction of the Apprenticeship Levy in 2017. We will set out further details about how this will operate in due course, including any programmes available for employers who will not pay the levy.</p><br /><p>We will also continue to offer employers an apprenticeship recruitment service through Find an Apprenticeship on gov.uk. We are continuing the Apprenticeship Grant for Employers (AGE) to support more small firms to take on 16-24 year old apprentices.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-14T16:06:30.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437970/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437970/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437970/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-14","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what programmes there are for companies who will not be covered by the Apprenticeship Levy to assist with the creation of apprenticeship positions; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","19944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437971","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-17","<p>We do not hold official statistics to the standard of the National Statistical Authority and so are unable to provide this information.</p><br /><p>Access to Work supported 36,760 disabled people to take up or remain in employment during 2014/15 (up from 35,560 in 2013/14).</p><br /> <br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-17T13:54:12.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437971/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437971/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437971/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-14","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many disabled people have benefitted from the Government's extension of the Access to Work scheme to cover work experience placements in the last two years; and how the £2 million allocated to that initiative has been spent.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","19987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437972","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-17","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-12-17T11:56:07.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437972/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437972/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437972/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-14","Mentally Disordered Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many psychiatric assessments have been requested by judges in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","19986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437973","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-17","<p>HM Revenue and Customs have no record of receiving a letter from the Hon Member dated 22 October regarding Working Tax Credit overpayments. However, if the Hon Member writes to me directly, I will ensure it gets a swift response.</p><br />","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-12-17T12:28:21.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437973/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437973/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437973/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-14","Revenue and Customs: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when HM Revenue and Customs plans to respond to the letter to that body from the hon. Member for Wolverhampton South West of 22 October 2015 on Working Tax Credit overpayment, case reference ZA1151.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","19789"
